title: [SPOILERS] The Fate of Cersei Lannister
body:
Maggy The Frog tells a young Cersei that “the valonqar (High Valerian for little brother) shall wrap his hands about your pale white throat and choke the life from you.”

This is probably why Cersei hates Tyrion so much as she believes that he will be the one to eventually kill her, destroying the Lannister family in the process. But I think that Jaime will be the one to kill her in S8 as he is the younger of the twins and that line is applicable to him as well. He finally realizes how batshit crazy she is (he probably does anyway) and that killing her the only way to avoid an repeat of another Mad Ruler.

Sorry if this has already been said but I just thought this was a cool little wrinkle that could add a plot twist to the final season. Cheers!



Source: http://bit.ly/2LFdv5P

summary: [Spoilers] Something I realized about Rob Stark
title: [Spoilers] Something I realized about Rob Stark
body:
So I was kind of thinking it was out of character for one of Ned starks son to break a vow like rob did by bluffing on marrying a Frey but I just realized the only vow rob thinks his father broke was having a bastard son. Idk I just think it’s soo fucking sad that rob thought that flaw would be okay for him too but like Ned never even cheated on catelyn stark he just said he did so Jon wouldn’t be murdered. Goddammit Jon all this pain and suffering better mean you’re the real Azor Azhai 😭 Sorry y’all I just watched the Red Wedding I’m a little upset
